title: Bump jquery-validation from 1.19.3 to 1.19.5
body:
Bumps [jquery-validation](https://github.com/jquery-validation/jquery-validation) from 1.19.3 to 1.19.5.
Release notes

Sourced from jquery-validation's releases.

1.19.5 / 2022-07-01

Chore

  • Add CodeQL analysis 3d3c1fb

Core

  • Fixed jQuery .submit() event shorthand deprecation notice #2430
  • Fixed ReDos vulnerability in url, and url2 validation 5bbd80d

Localisation

  • Added periods to messages #2266

1.19.4 / 2022-05-19

Build

  • Add License.md to zip tarball (#2386)

Chore

  • Updated build status badges (#2424)
  • Enabled stable bot (#2425)

Core

  • Fixed validation for input type="date" (#2360)
  • Wait for pendingRequests to finish before submitting form (#2369)
  • Fixed bug for Html Editors (#2154) (#2422)
  • Fixed ReDoS vulnerability in URL2 validation (#2428)

Test

  • Switch from Travis to GitHub workflows (#2423)

title: WIP: NEW Add BulkDeleteFormSubmissionsJob
body: Provides a way for admins to utilise `silverstripe-queuedjobs` to remove form submissions by specifying a cutoff date (submissions older than this will be removed including uploaded files). The job can also be rescheduled and reuse the specified cutoff date. Lastly, an option to specify the userform page ID (ParentID) where the form submission is associated to can be set to remove only specific submissions.

body:
Previously hard coded size of 1MB meant any file larger was excluded
from recipient emails - often confusing for CMS admins configuring an
advanced use case for a userform, expecting to recieve files to begin a
business process external to the website.

resolves #1008

title: Check if file is uploaded in a more robust way
body:
Hi,
I'm not sure if it is due to my PHP version (7.3.7), but the $_FILES is not empty when an upload field is present but no file is uploaded by the user.
Based on https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12538718/files-array-is-not-empty-upon-uploading-nothing and https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.is-uploaded-file.php, I've added a different way of checking if a file is uploaded before trying to create the Upload object.
Also, the Upload->->loadIntoFile method can return false, so I've added a check fo that too, however, not sure what is meant to happen in that case. It is more likely that a bad file with throw an error caught by the try catch.
Also, checking that the $file is valid object before trying to write it.
